{"title_page": "Spritmonitor", "text_new": "{{Infobox website\n| logo          = Logo of Spritmonitor.png\n| name          = Spritmonitor\n| url           = [http://www.spritmonitor.de/en/ www.spritmonitor.de]\n| language = German, English, French, Spanish\n| registration = Optional\n| owner    = Fisch und Fischl GmbH\n| num_users = 560,000\n| launch_date    = January 2001\n}}\n\n'''Spritmonitor''' is a German [[website]] that collects and delivers information about the [[Fuel economy in automobiles|fuel consumption]] of vehicles under real-life conditions. The data base is provided by the users of the website themselves ([[crowdsourcing]]) who log the fuel ups of their vehicles in the system.\n\n== History ==\nThe website was created by Thomas Fischl and Dominik Fisch as a side project to their study of computer science at the [[University of Passau]], [[Germany]] in 2001.<ref>[http://www.uni-passau.de/bereiche/presse/pressemeldungen/meldung/detail/der-wahre-spritverbrauch-auf-spritmonitorde/ ''Der wahre Spritverbrauch auf Spritmonitor.de''] University of Passau. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref> Initially, the project was known under the name \u201eConsumption Tables\u201c and was renamed to \u201eSpritmonitor\u201c after a testing phase (\u201eSprit\u201c is in Germany colloquial speech for fuel). The website is operated and owned by the ''Fisch und Fischl GmbH'' company which was founded in 2008.\n\n== Functions == \nSpritmonitor offers two main functions:\n\nFirst, it is possible for a car owner to log and track fuel up data and all vehicle based expenses in the system. Based on this data many different analyses can be performed (e.g., fuel consumption depending on season, kind of fuel, used tires, etc.).<ref>[http://www.spritmonitor.de/de/funktionen_von_spritmonitor.html ''Funktionen von Spritmonitor''] Spritmonitor. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.aachener-zeitung.de/news/auto/autoverbrauch-website-sammelt-daten-1.546216 ''Autoverbrauch: Website sammelt Daten''] Aachener Zeitung. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref> Spritmonitor can be used on the road with the corresponding [[iPhone]]-, [[Android operating system|Android]]-, and [[Microsoft Windows Phone|Windows Phone]]-Apps as well as with the mobile version of the website.\n\nSecond, the data base entries of Spritmonitor users can be viewed and analysed by others. Thereby, future car owners do not only have to rely on the fuel consumption published by car manufacturers but they can also get information about the to be expected real-life fuel consumption of a vehicle before buying it.\n\n== Use in scientific studies and tests ==\nThe Spritmonitor data base has reached such a significance in size and quality that it can be used in scientific studies. The [[International Council on Clean Transportation|ICCT]] uses the data set in its annual report \u201cFrom Laboratory To Road\u201d <ref>[http://www.theicct.org/sites/default/files/publications/ICCT_LaboratoryToRoad_2014_Report_English.pdf ''From Laboratory To Road 2014''] ICCT. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.theicct.org/sites/default/files/publications/ICCT_LaboratoryToRoad_2015_Report_English.pdf ''From Laboratory To Road 2015''] ICCT. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.theicct.org/sites/default/files/publications/ICCT_LaboratoryToRoad_2016.pdf ''From Laboratory To Road 2016''] ICCT. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref> as well as [[Transport and Environment]] in its annual study \u201cMind The Gap\u201d.<ref>[https://www.transportenvironment.org/sites/te/files/publications/TE_Mind_the_Gap_2015_FINAL.pdf ''Mind The Gap 2015''] Transport and Environment. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[https://www.transportenvironment.org/sites/te/files/publications/T%26E_Mind_the_Gap_2016%20FINAL_0.pdf ''Mind The Gap 2016''] Transport and Environment. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref> Also the [[Deutsche Umwelthilfe]] refers to Spritmonitor in its publication \u201cVerbrauchsabweichungen in Deutschland und den USA\u201d.<ref>[http://www.duh.de/uploads/media/DUH_Hintergrund-Mehrverbrauch_Vergleich_D-USA_2015-02-26.pdf ''Verbrauchsabweichungen in Deutschland und den USA''] Deutsche Umwelthilfe. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref>\n\nBesides those scientific studies, the Spritmonitor data is also used in vehicles tests of different media.<ref>[https://www.heise.de/autos/artikel/Renault-Zoe-mit-41-kWh-Batterie-3334740.html ''Renault Zoe mit 41 kWh-Batterie''] heise Autos. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.zeit.de/wirtschaft/2014-09/mini-cooper ''Mini Cooper''] Zeit Online. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.zeit.de/auto/2012-08/ford-focus ''Ford Focus''] Zeit Online. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref><ref>[http://www.focus.de/auto/experten/duennes/oekobilanz-von-elektroautos-besser-als-benzin-oder-oekologisches-feigenblatt-so-sauber-ist-ein-elektroauto-wirklich_id_4914399.html ''\u00d6kobilanz von Elektroautos''] Focus Online. Retrieved February 26, 2017.</ref> The German consumer organisation [[Stiftung Warentest]] also references Spritmonitor in their guide to buying used cars.<ref>[https://www.test.de/Gebrauchtwagen-Augen-auf-beim-Gebrauchtwagenkauf-4989259-0/ ''So gehen Sie klug vor beim Gebrauchtwagenkauf''] Stiftung Warentest. Retrieved January 5, 2020.</ref>\n\n== Figures ==\nThe Spritmonitor data base contains over 830,000 vehicles of 560,000 users. All the users together logged over 32 million fuel ups which correspond to a driven distance of 16 billion kilometres.<ref>[http://www.spritmonitor.de/en/ ''Spritmonitor''] Spritmonitor. Retrieved April 6, 2020.</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:German websites]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox website\n| logo          = Logo of Spritmonitor.png\n| name          = Spritmonitor\n| url           = [http://www.spritmonitor.de/en/ www.spritmonitor.de]\n| language = German, English, French, Spanish\n| registration = Optional\n| owner    = Fisch un